        <section class="description" id="description">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-history"></i> About Durgam Cheruvu</h2>
            <p>Durgam Cheruvu, also known as the "Secret Lake," is a serene freshwater lake located in the heart of Hyderabad's bustling IT corridor. Spanning approximately 63 acres, this hidden gem is surrounded by rocky granite hills, offering a peaceful escape from the urban hustle.</p>

            <div class="historical-fact">
                The lake is believed to have been constructed during the Qutb Shahi dynasty to serve as a water source for the Golconda Fort. Its name "Durgam" (meaning difficult) refers to its hidden location, which was once hard to access.
            </div>

            <p>Today, Durgam Cheruvu is a popular spot for locals and tourists alike, offering activities like boating, rock climbing, and nature walks. The lake is also a haven for birdwatchers, with several migratory birds visiting the area seasonally.</p>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 20px; color: var(--hyderabad-blue);"><i class="fas fa-leaf"></i> Key Features</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>Boating facilities including pedal boats and water scooters</li>
                <li>Walking and jogging tracks around the lake</li>
                <li>Adventure activities like rock climbing and rappelling</li>
                <li>Amphitheater for cultural events and performances</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

